variables.name: GENERIC_FAILURE
variables.comment:
* GENERIC_FAILURE is used for failure that don't fit
     * into one of the other categories.

variables.name: WRITE_FAILURE
variables.comment: * WRITE_FAILURE is used when a write to an output stream fails.

variables.name: FLUSH_FAILURE
variables.comment: * FLUSH_FAILURE is used when a flush to an output stream fails.

variables.name: CLOSE_FAILURE
variables.comment: * CLOSE_FAILURE is used when a close of an output stream fails.

variables.name: OPEN_FAILURE
variables.comment: * OPEN_FAILURE is used when an open of an output stream fails.

variables.name: FORMAT_FAILURE
variables.comment: * FORMAT_FAILURE is used when formatting fails for any reason.

methods.name: public synchronized void error(String msg, Exception ex, int code)
methods.comment:
* The error method is called when a Handler failure occurs. *

* This method may be overridden in subclasses. The default * behavior in this base class is that the first call is * reported to System.err, and subsequent calls are ignored. * * @param msg a descriptive string (may be null) * @param ex an exception (may be null) * @param code an error code defined in ErrorManager

methodNames: public synchronized void error(String msg, Exception ex, int code)
